--- title: "Get environmental data for the occurrence locationa" --- We need to get a data frame with the environmental data for the occurrence locations. ## Set up ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} library(ggplot2) library(sdmpredictors) ``` ::: Set the directory where we will save environmental data layers. ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} dir_env <- here::here("data", "env") options(sdmpredictors_datadir = dir_env) ``` ::: ## Add datasets We will use the sdmpredictors R package which has marine data layers. ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} # choose marine env_datasets <- sdmpredictors::list_datasets(terrestrial = FALSE, marine = TRUE) ``` ::: ## Show the available variables The dataframe is large. We will use the DT package to make the table pretty in html. ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} env_layers <- sdmpredictors::list_layers(env_datasets$dataset_code) DT::datatable(env_layers) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}
